# BMad — titres des conversations Agents

When Guillaume starts a conversation with a **BMad skill** (attached skill or slash command such as `/bmad-create-story`, `/bmad-dev-story`, `/bmad-code-review`, `/bmad-correct-course`, etc.), **rename the current chat immediately** — as the **first tool call**, before any other work.

Also apply on **resume**: if Guillaume sends a message in an existing BMad conversation whose title is still the auto-generated one (e.g. `Story creation process`, `Code review discussion`, `bmad dev story 4-4`) instead of the BMad format below, call `rename_chat` first — infer skill and story ID from the conversation's first user message (attached skill or slash command).

Use the MCP tool `rename_chat` on server `cursor-app-control`. **Only this API persists the title** — direct database edits to the sidebar cache are overwritten when the conversation is opened (Cursor reloads the title from the conversation checkpoint).

## Title format

`BMad {Workflow Label} {Story ID}` — omit `{Story ID}` when none is provided.

**Never append a date** (e.g. `(2026-06-19)`) to the title. The Agents sidebar already shows when each conversation occurred (`Today`, `2d`, etc.). Duplicate runs of the same workflow share the same title — the sidebar timestamp is enough to tell them apart.

